This is a known breaking change. Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30+), and .NET 10 MAUI removed the old platform-specific API that wrapped it. The modern fix is to listen to **window insets** on Android and adjust your layout padding accordingly.

### Solution

**1. In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`**, set the soft input mode and subscribe to inset changes:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Platform.Compatibility;

[Activity(/* ...existing attributes... */,
          WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustNothing)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for keyboard (IME) insets
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
            Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object,
        IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(
            View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(
                WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Bottom padding = keyboard height (or nav bar if closed)
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**2. Your XAML chat page** — put the input bar at the bottom of a `Grid`:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0"
                    ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}"
                    ItemsUpdatingScrollMode="KeepLastItemInView" />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

### Why this works

| Old approach | New approach |
|---|---|
| `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` — OS resizes the window | `AdjustNothing` + `WindowInsetsCompat` — you control the padding |

The inset listener fires whenever the keyboard opens/closes, giving you the exact pixel height. Setting bottom padding on the decor view pushes your entire MAUI layout up above the keyboard.

### iOS

No changes needed — iOS MAUI already adjusts for the keyboard by default via safe area insets.
